
/*
 * The provided Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to use the [add] slot to append nodes to a collection. It retrieves nodes using [get-nodes] from the [.arguments] node, specifically targeting [limit] and [offset] arguments, and adds them to the [data.read] node. This is useful for dynamically modifying a node structure based on input arguments.
 * 
 * 1. [add] - Appends nodes to the specified node collection.
 * 2. [get-nodes] - Retrieves nodes from the [.arguments] node, specifically [limit] and [offset].
 */
add:x:./*/data.read
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/limit
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/offset
